s": {"772f79c9-c542-4652-8079-b78e4bdfe43c_89387719": 80.0}}, {"text": "Increased ocean heat can cause wide-scale coral bleaching, death of marine life, and elevation of sea level.", "citations": {"772f79c9-c542-4652-8079-b78e4bdfe43c_89387719": 80.0}}, {"text": "\"Biological removal of CO2 through primary production can help offset the negative impact of ocean acidification, and international cooperation is necessary to address this global issue.\"", "citations": {"574849e9-6f52-48ce-9c63-44f3d756ba1c_158383503": 80.0}}, {"text": "Ocean acidification kills marine life and affects biodiversity by disrupting the ocean's pH balance and impacting creatures that rely on calcium for their shells and skeletons.", "citations": {"772f79c9-c542-4652-8079-b78e4bdfe43c_89387719": 80.0}}, {"text": "The study on ocean acidification was published in Scientific Reports, a reputable scientific journal.", "citations": {"d14dd391-897a-4a7b-8853-c26120e4f894_74574488": 80.0}}, {"text": "Ocean acidification affects the early life stages of marine life, including oysters.", "citations": {"df975b8e-3549-4522-a603-ff92fe192723_316177390": 80.0}}, {"text": "Climate change affects marine life by decreasing ocean oxygen levels.", "citations": {"d9dfdce9-4d22-443a-b5e5-c34681d22386_853366889": 80.0}}, {"text": "Ocean acidification can lead to thinner and smaller shells in marine organisms, as seen in the reduced shell growth of clams grown in acidified conditions.", "citations": {"0f12f37d-8df3-4e5d-90c5-d3860ba8d4a2_872534487": 80.0}}, {"text": "Ocean acidification threatens marine calcifiers like clams, mussels, and oysters by making it harder for them to form calcium carbonate, necessary for their growth.", "citations": {"fb3ce5ea-13a3-4890-876c-318b8385b408_446340951": 80.0}}, {"text": "Ocean acidification affects the growth of shelled marine animals like oysters, clams, crabs, and lobsters by making it harder for them to form calcium carbonate.", "citations": {"fb3ce5ea-13a3-4890-876c-318b8385b408_446340951": 80.0}}, {"text": "Ocean acidification has increased by 26% since pre-industrial times, with a predicted rise of 100 to 150% by the end of the century, having severe effects on marine life.", "citations": {"fd3cffd4-e1c0-49e9-af0e-b2a04d515360_1027225775": 80.0}}, {"text": "Ocean acidification hinders shell growth in marine life by reducing calcium and carbonate ions.", "citations": {"772f79c9-c542-4652-8079-b78e4bdfe43c_89387719": 80.0}}], "references": ["d9dfdce9-4d22-443a-b5e5-c34681d22386_853366889", "fd3cffd4-e1c0-49e9-af0e-b2a04d515360_1027225775", "df975b8e-3549-4522-a603-ff92fe192723_316177390", "772f79c9-c542-4652-8079-b78e4bdfe43c_89387719", "fb3ce5ea-13a3-4890-876c-318b8385b408_446340951", "0f12f37d-8df3-4e5d-90c5-d3860ba8d4a2_872534487", "d14dd391-897a-4a7b-8853-c26120e4f894_74574488", "574849e9-6f52-48ce-9c63-44f3d756ba1c_158383503"]}
