"8c32d1ae-e169-4582-9fd1-e5448e2b55a6_1005984929": 80.0}}, {"text": "\"Antibiotics are being replaced as an additive in animal feed, potentially including salmon feed, due to safety concerns and are being substituted with microbial biologics like probiotics, prebiotics, and symbiotics.\"", "citations": {"bb4fd768-e7a4-414b-9c8b-25e59edc3aa7_414881958": 80.0}}, {"text": "\"Plant-based ingredients, such as those derived from coix seeds and algae, are being used as a replacement for antibiotics in salmon feed due to their natural antimicrobial properties.\"", "citations": {"88e1620b-05e4-4676-b96c-ba056e1a081f_297756784": 80.0}}, {"text": "The country where feed additives are managed is Taiwan, with various management methods in place for different environments.", "citations": {"dac92579-02ed-4386-a62d-cf5602790d9c_557147700": 80.0}}, {"text": "\"Common feed acidifiers used in salmon farming include formic acid, citric acid, and propionic acid, which are used to improve feed quality and reduce bacterial growth.\"", "citations": {"f5d0e854-eb55-4d44-ab24-b5048804780e_793015685": 80.0}}, {"text": "\"Traditional single species fish farms often use antibiotics and additives, but some are adopting more natural approaches like probiotics to promote fish health.\"", "citations": {"206276b7-7de2-4dab-9189-36c5eec717e8_576973288": 80.0}}, {"text": "\"Amino acids like methionine are added to feed to increase its nutritional value and support animal growth and metabolism.\"", "citations": {"33253149-3071-4359-aa80-aa606ec11c77_458600762": 80.0}}, {"text": "The goal of replacing antibiotics with natural ingredients in salmon feed is to produce healthier fish by reducing the risk of antibiotic resistance.", "citations": {"88e1620b-05e4-4676-b96c-ba056e1a081f_297756784": 80.0}}, {"text": "Lactobacillus B4 is a probiotic used in fish feed to enhance growth and improve resistance to pathogens.", "citations": {"206276b7-7de2-4dab-9189-36c5eec717e8_576973288": 90.0}}, {"text": "The types of Omega 3 fatty acids found in farmed salmon are EPA and DHA.", "citations": {"e9e0e25f-b317-4e99-8bf7-431ab1e290be_110862371": 100.0}}, {"text": "The bacteria used for producing feed additives in the new technology is Bacillus subtilis, which can be easily grown on waste grain production.", "citations": {"bb4fd768-e7a4-414b-9c8b-25e59edc3aa7_414881958": 100.0}}], "references": ["bb4fd768-e7a4-414b-9c8b-25e59edc3aa7_414881958", "88e1620b-05e4-4676-b96c-ba056e1a081f_297756784", "206276b7-7de2-4dab-9189-36c5eec717e8_576973288", "33253149-3071-4359-aa80-aa606ec11c77_458600762", "8c32d1ae-e169-4582-9fd1-e5448e2b55a6_1005984929", "dac92579-02ed-4386-a62d-cf5602790d9c_557147700", "e9e0e25f-b317-4e99-8bf7-431ab1e290be_110862371", "f5d0e854-eb55-4d44-ab24-b5048804780e_793015685"]}
