10": 80.0}}, {"text": "\"Antibiotics are being replaced as an additive in animal feed, potentially including salmon feed, due to safety concerns and are being substituted with microbial biologics like probiotics, prebiotics, and symbiotics.\"", "citations": {"bb4fd768-e7a4-414b-9c8b-25e59edc3aa7_414881958": 80.0}}, {"text": "Antibiotics are being replaced as an additive in salmon feed, with alternatives like bacteria Bacillus subtilis and bran being developed.", "citations": {"bb4fd768-e7a4-414b-9c8b-25e59edc3aa7_414881958": 80.0}}, {"text": "\"Antibiotics are commonly used additives in salmon feed, but there is a trend towards replacing them with more natural alternatives to reduce dependence on antibiotics.\"", "citations": {"88e1620b-05e4-4676-b96c-ba056e1a081f_297756784": 80.0}}, {"text": "Antibiotics are often used in salmon feed but are being replaced due to health concerns and environmental impacts.", "citations": {"39b66508-c08e-45cc-aca1-ebcd84856d91_226266469": 80.0}}, {"text": "\"Plant-based ingredients, such as those derived from coix seeds and algae, are being used as a replacement for antibiotics in salmon feed due to their natural antimicrobial properties.\"", "citations": {"88e1620b-05e4-4676-b96c-ba056e1a081f_297756784": 80.0}}, {"text": "The country where feed additives are managed is Taiwan, with various management methods in place for different environments.", "citations": {"dac92579-02ed-4386-a62d-cf5602790d9c_557147700": 80.0}}, {"text": "\"Common feed acidifiers used in salmon farming include formic acid, citric acid, and propionic acid, which are used to improve feed quality and reduce bacterial growth.\"", "citations": {"f5d0e854-eb55-4d44-ab24-b5048804780e_793015685": 80.0}}, {"text": "Common feed acidifiers used in salmon farming include formic acid, citric acid, and propionic acid, which are added to feeds to decrease the pH and prevent harmful intestinal microflora from growing.", "citations": {"f5d0e854-eb55-4d44-ab24-b5048804780e_79301